ooks like this:\r\n\r\n````\r\npublic class MyApp extends ControllerApplication {\r\n    protected void onInit() {\r\n        registerContentTypeEngine(IsoDateGsonEngine.class);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * Dirty hack to adjust Pippos default configuration for Gson.\r\n */\r\npublic class IsoDateGsonEngine extends GsonEngine {\r\n\r\n    private final Gson gson;\r\n\r\n    public IsoDateGsonEngine() {\r\n        gson = new GsonBuilder().registerTypeAdapter(Date.class, new ISO8601DateTypeAdapter()).create();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public String toString(Object object) {\r\n        return gson.toJson(object);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public <T> T fromString(String content, Class<T> classOfT) {\r\n        return gson.fromJson(content, classOfT);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n````\r\n\r\nBoy – am I wrong. This does not work, because [the Service Locator infrastructure in `Application`](https://github.com/decebals/pippo/blob/master/pippo-core/src/main/java/ro/pippo/core/Application.java#L105) finds the [`GsonInitializer`](https://github.com/decebals/pippo/blob/master/pippo-content-type-parent/pippo-gson/src/main/java/ro/pippo/gson/GsonInitializer.java) and adds the default configuration on its own. Furthermore there is no way to _replace_ or _remove_ a preexisting content type handler. The [code actively ignores that](https://github.com/decebals/pippo/blob/master/pippo-core/src/main/java/ro/pippo/core/ContentTypeEngines.java#L102).\r\n\r\nAny idea how to tackle that?","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pippo-java/pippo/issues/411","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pippo-java/pippo","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pippo-java/pippo/issues/411/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pippo-java/pippo/issues/411/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pippo-java/pippo/issues/411/events","html_url":"https://github.com/pippo-java/pippo/issues/411","id":285407712,"number":411,"title":"PippoRunTimeException on using Controllers